cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for the detection and recognition of immunogold particles in electron microscopy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of stacked denoising autoencoders and transfer learning also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image retrieval and analysis, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
